<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,752,851]" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">
This is a relatively large 
<collectingCountry box="[433,528,752,778]" name="Vietnam" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
endemic species, somewhat resembling 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[988,1087,752,778]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis box="[988,1087,752,778]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">M. heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[1144,1261,752,778]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="13" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distans">
<emphasis box="[1144,1261,752,778]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">M. distans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of appendages but unique in the shape of the genital ligula with relatively long and thin horns (
<figureCitation box="[1189,1299,788,815]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1443,1467]" captionTargetBox="[175,1424,244,1412]" captionTargetId="figure-56@15.[151,1437,237,1419]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 4. Caudal appendages of males (lateral view). a) australis; b) irma, paratype; c) distans, from Yaan, Sichuan; d) distans from Qingchengshan, Chengdu, Sichuan; e) heros; f) omeiensis, paratype; g) kurahashii; h) major; i) haui; j) “palaceus”; k) micans; l) “Chengi,” paratype; m) riccii; n) maai; o) tuska, from Damingshan, Guangxi; p) tuska, from Jinxiu, Guangxi. (Scale bar = 0.5 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407493" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407493/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Fig. 4a, n</figureCitation>
). Its species status was supported by molecular analyses (
<figureCitation box="[654,722,824,851]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[213,1367,496,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-214@20.[211,1375,489,1954]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Phylogenetic reconstruction from ITS data modified based on BI and ML trees, with both posterior probabilities (right) and bootstrap values (left) shown." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407499/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="258">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
